channel.title: Little Help
channel.description:
Hey. Got back into SCAR and tried to re-arrange all my folders. Got so far, so good, and I get this error:
[code]Line 26: [Error] (64:1): Duplicate identifier 'UpChars' in script C:\Program Files\SCAR 3.01\includes\srl\srl\core\Globals.scar[/code]
What does it mean?
Thanks.

item.title: Little Help
item.dc:creator: @dudeofthed dudeofthed
item.description:
@dudeofthed wrote:

[quote=“Freddy1990, post:3, topic:82587”]Try to press “Download SRL” in the File menu again…
Do mind that SCAR Divi 3.02 has already been released (http://freddy1990.com/scar.php)[/quote]
I didn’t Spam. My message is inside the quote and forgot to remove it and put it into an actual post. Sorry.

The original message that i was meant to put was “For some reason, in the new SCAR Divi version. That error ahs kept popping up to me too. I think it has even been popping up on everyone else’s too. So, just use the older version of scar 2.03 until this issue can be fixed.”.
